description:
Job Description

Drive the business of Local sales and leasing Property;
Achieve sales target set by the Management;
Approach new client and build relationship with them; maintain close relationship with existing client;
Implement business strategies, plans and procedures set out by the Management;
Work with other department such as Marketing/International Project team on business initiatives
Assist to prepare business reports and attend meetings with senior management as requested;
Identify new business opportunity and strategies to Manager

The Successful Applicant

Proficient in English, Cantonese and Mandarin is a must
Excellent communication, customer service, and interpersonal skill
Responsible, analytical minded, results oriented individual with good business acumen
Two years sales experience in luxury property preferred
EAA licence is required

Responsibilities

Manage and oversee the operations of property management services;
Supervise a team to provide quality property management services to clients;
Ensure compliance with relevant ordinance and regulations;
Liaise with clients, supplier and internal parties;
Handle ad hoc assignments as required

Requirements

Degree holder or above in property management or related disciplines;
Member of CIH / HKIH is preferred or other recognized professional bodies;
Holder of provisional PMP License (Tier 1) is preferred;
5 years or above relevant experience in property management of which 2 years should be at managerial level;
Strong leadership, communication, and interpersonal skills;
Proficient in both written and spoken English and Chinese

Candidates with less experience will be considered for the post of Senior Property Officer.

Responsibilities:

Negotiate with clients on lease terms and conditions for new and renewal leases;
Process admission applications and tenancy renewals from site visits to preparation of lease documentations on a timely and efficient manner;
Conduct tenant visit regularly and offer value added service to tenants;
Liaise with potential or existing tenants on admission and renewal matters;
Coordinate with internal departments to facilitate the admission and expansion of tenants;
Perform any other duties as assigned by supervisor.

Requirements:

Possession of a Bachelor Degree in Real Estate, Property Management, Business Administration or related disciplines;
4 - 5 years’ relevant working experience in leasing administration operation;
Good communication, interpersonal and negotiation skills;
Self-motivated, customer-oriented, self-disciplined and systematic;
Excellent planning, attention to details and result driven;
Pleasant, outgoing and enthusiastic;
Proficiency in both written and spoken English and Chinese (including Putonghua).

We offer market competitive compensation, 5-day work week, and generous benefits including medical and life insurance; and voluntary contribution in addition to the legal minimum MPF. To apply, please send your full resume with current and expected salary to the Human Resources & Office Administration Department, Hong Kong Science and Technology Parks Corporation, 5/F, Building 5E, 5 Science Park East Avenue, Hong Kong Science Park, Hong Kong or, by email via "Apply Now" on or before 20 January 2021. Please quote the reference number on the email subject/envelope and the application letter. 

Personal data provided will be treated in strict confidence and used for recruitment purpose only.  All personal data collected will be used strictly in accordance with employer’s personal data policies, you can access to HKSTP’s Personal Information Collection Statement at https://www.hkstp.org/hkstp_web/en/hkstp/personal-information-collection-statement-recruitment

Applicants not invited for interview within four weeks after application deadline may consider their applications unsuccessful.  Personal data of unsuccessful applicants will be retained for a maximum of two years. 

